      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of May 7 Magainze article about Americans' belief in their potential; response of blacks noted</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Because of an editing error, an article in The Times Magazine last Sunday about Americans' belief in their potential misstated the response of African-Americans to a poll question about the effect of race in shaping identity. Three-quarters of African-Americans said that Americans can be what they want to be or close to it. They did not say that race plays ''not much role'' in the identities of Americans.</p>
      </block>
